description.1: Conan joins Bengala, "Protectress of Tigers", to stop the Maharadjah from killing all the tigers in his domain.
description.3: Who are they? What part of the galaxy do they come from? What do they want? Han, Luke, and Leia better find out-or face total disaster!
description.5: The Black Fox is captured by the Red Ghost and his Super-Apes! Spider-Man rescues Fox, but must face the wrath of the Apes! Elsewhere, an old enemy once thought dead waits to ambush the wall-crawler!
description.6: With the threat from outer space taken care of, Earth's Mightiest Heroes get back to rebuilding the team's assets. First on the list: a new place to call HQ!
description.7: The hunt for Baron Zemo continues as Captain America and Nomad travel deeper into darkness! Plus: Cap's been poisoned with a serum that causing him to age rapidly. Will the Star-Spangled Avenger manage to defeat Mother Superior before it's too late!
description.12: Watching from the shadows, the Kingpin at last unleashes his newest enforcer on an unsuspecting Spider-Man!
description.13: Ben Grimm realizes he is a prisoner of his own mind, when things are not as they seem while investigating Doomstadt!
description.15: A very special tale starring the ever-lovin', blue-eyed Thing, by comics legend Barry Windsor-Smith! Then, follow DAREDEVIL as he investigates a mysterious string of arsons!
description.17: You've seen ol' Hornhead in New York - you've seen him in San Francisco - you've even seen him in Japan! But you've never seen him in a predicament like this!
description.18: Wedding bells are ringing in Attilan, the home of the Inhumans! At long last Black Bolt and Medusa are getting married! And of course the Fantastic Four are invited! It looks like a wonderful day in the Blue Area of the Moon, but the Inhumans remember what happened the last time there was a royal wedding (in Fantastic Four #150)! Sure enough two mighty warriors, one from the Kree Empire and the other from the Skrull Empire, interrupt the ceremony! They don't care about the wedding; they just care about winning their epic one-on-one battle! However, to achieve everlasting peace, Mr. Fantastic, Black Bolt, and the Watcher put together a plan to make winners out of both warriors! Cameo appearance by Wolverine.
description.19: Hang in there, Tony Stark! You may have lost control of your fortune, your super-hero identity, and your international prestige, but things aren't always what they seem!
description.21: She-Hulk reveals her origins while taking a tour of the Baxter Building with Johnny. But the tour is interrupted...by a mysterious assailant!
description.22: After Colossus breaks up with Kitty, Wolverine takes him into town for a good ol' talking-to. And that's precisely when the Juggernaut shows up!
description.23: The Hobgoblin's battlewagon is hauled up from the Hudson River and stolen by Jack O' Lantern! Using the Spider-tracer he previously put on the van, Spider-Man searches for Jack. A battle ensues!
description.24: It's an all-out battle for the Avengers as they race against the clock to stop the aliens from carrying out their mission. Wasp and Captain Marvel must figure out of way of getting the space ship to return safely into the Earth's atmosphere. Will they succeed? Or will the crashing space-craft cause mass destruction?
description.25: Captain America's world comes crumbling down when Baron Zemo and Mother Superior put their plans in motion. With the lives of two loved at risk Captain America must race against the time to figure just what the Mother Superior and Baron Zemo are up to!
description.26: Victor Kreeger antagonizes as the ‘Hammer of Judgment’! Even thick-skinned Power Man takes some slugs in this one!
description.29: Conan the Barbarian has become Conan the cowardly! What could have caused Conan to change? Find out!
description.32: Bet you didn't know that Chewbacca had a wife and family! But he may never get to see them again-when bloodthirsty bounty-hunters attack him on his way back to the Wookiee planet! And if Lando and Han can't help-who can?
description.33: With the barbarian Tarianna by his side, Ben approaches another planet's version of Doomstadt.
description.38: A lovers' quarrel! Black Cat isn't sure how she feels about the all-new Spider-Man, but they'll have to hash that out later - if the BLOB doesn't crush them first!
description.39: The Black Widow is a hostage of Hydra! Daredevil is in for the fight of his life to save the woman he loves.
description.40: Tony Stark perseveres against obstacles which can crush his very soul! And it's still nothing compared to what Iron Man has to face!
description.43: Reed goes against his gut and seeks the aid of Doctor Octopus. But can Reed keep Doc Ock on task long enough to save his wife and unborn child?
description.44: Rogue attacks a SHIELD helicarrier after learning of Michael Rossi's capture. Could Rogue's recent absorption of Carol Danver's powers and memories be getting the better of her?
description.46: Doctor Strange helps the Priests of Bjarghan determine whether or not they are “The Chosen One.”
description.48: Inhumans Medusa and Lockjaw seek out Dazzler for help, but the mutant pop star turns them away for a life sans super-heroics!
description.49: When Solo comes across a rare artifact, it will lead into the rediscovery of a planet long since destroyed...but why does this planet still exist?
description.50: For his latest journalist assignment, Peter goes to a football game to snap pictures. He discovers that scandal involving the Rose is underway! Peter decides to break the news to Aunt May about graduate school. Can Spidey deal with upsetting the ones he loves?
description.51: Responding to suspected extraterrestrial sabotage at the Kennedy Space Center, the Avengers are on hand to stop a group of terrorists called the Rocketeers! Can the Avengers get to the bottom of this space mystery?
description.52: The fight with the Slayer continues! But things escalate when Mother Superior enters the fray! Plus: Who are the Sisters of Sin?
description.55: The Heroes for Hire battle Whirlwind! Will Power Man and Iron Fist be able to stand their ground when Whirlwind summons up a storm?
description.57: An epic interview with Archie Goodwin!
description.58: Hercules returns to Mount Olympus where Zeus has murdered all the inhabitants. There's only one name left on his hit list: Hercules himself.
description.60: Mike Zeck has gotten some of Marvel's biggest and baddest heroes riled up and looking for a scrape. You don't want to mess with this bunch, trust us. The Beyonder learned that the hard way.
description.63: Spotlight on the Black Cat! She's looking for her on-and-off lover Spidey, but what she finds is going to change her relationship with him forever!
description.64: While in Battleworld, Ben has his transporter device stolen by one of the Takers!
description.68: Debbie Nelson, Foggy’s wife, is in deep trouble thanks to the machinations of Micah Synn!
description.69: Tony Stark has to make the most important decision of his life. Meanwhile, Rhodey has returned from his mysterious disappearance with all-new armor!
description.71: Reed, alongside other Marvel geniuses, works round the clock to find a solution to Sue's complicated pregnancy. Alicia recalls Ben's first meeting with the mysterious Karisma.
description.72: With the help of Sunfire, the X-Men battle a terrible beast in Japan. Meanwhile, Senator Kelly proposes the Mutant Control Act in Washington.
description.73: Hercules is summoned to Titan, where a dying Apollo warns his brother of their father's insanity.
description.74: Lando goes out to meet an old flame and ends up in the middle of a planetary war!
description.78: Spider-Man is back from Battleworld and he's wearing a new suit! Artist Ron Frenz took the classic pose of Spidey from AMAZING FANTASY #15, made a few adjustments, and the result was a cover almost--if not just as--iconic as the original.
description.79: With all of his teammates missing in action, the Vision, acting as the Avengers' Chairman must try to quell public panic. But when the absence of his teammates looks to be permanent the Vision declares a new team of Avengers must rise! Enter: The West Coast Avengers!
description.80: While out on a routine search for crime, Cap and Nomad are viciously attacked by a familiar face, Dave Cox. Now calling himself the Slayer, a bloodthirsty Dave vows to put an end to Captain America and all who stand beside him!
description.81: The arrival of a new hero, Crime-Buster, brings fresh competition to the Heroes for Hire!
description.82: An exclusive interview with John Byrne! Plus, previews of POWER PACK!
description.83: Ben is tormented over his love for Alicia. His musings are interrupted when Reed calls the Thing into action to investigate strange energies in Central Park…
description.87: Glorianna O'Breen seeks refuge in New York, but her “sanctuary status” may be short-lived once she starts chasing leads from the past.
description.88: Having fought for his life among the Pyramids, you'd think that Iron Man would take it easy for a while! Rhodey's up to his transistors in action, while Tony Stark is up against the Mandarin.
description.91: The Fantastic Four welcome She-Hulk as it's newest member, replacing The Thing! Meanwhile, Trapster roams the Baxter Building...but will he find what he’s looking for?
description.92: A trip to the Massachusetts Academy turns disastrous for Kitty Pryde and Doug Ramsey.
description.94: Lights out! When a blackout hits the city, looters begin robbing Jack Zelnick's pawn shop and the night ends fatally. Can Spider-Man and Matt Murdock find the true criminals?
description.95: Strange stands off against an unusual threat—while protecting innocents and scrambling for his own survival!
description.97: With Doombringer nowhere in sight, Power Man and Iron Fist are pressed to find him before he ushers forth Armageddon!
description.99: An overview of Jim Starlin’s cosmic Marvel Comics career!

2.text: The Power siblings - Alexander, Julie, Jack, and Katherine are rescued by a Whitemane creature from the evil Snarks who kidnapped their parents! The Power Pack is born!

8.text: Hulk continues to regress into a savage state. Which hero will rise to the occasion to help Banner undergo a heroic transformation?

9.text: TEMPEST WITHOUT, CRISIS WITHIN Doctor Doom creates two new villains Called Volcana and Titania to take the heroes down! Meanwhile, Spider-Man battles the X-Men!

10.text: Something is causing the citizens of New York to crumble to dust. What is the reason for this mysterious and lethal transformation? Can Thor stop it?

11.text: The shocking death of longtime Alpha Flight commander Guardian.

12.text: Watching from the shadows, the Kingpin at last unleashes his newest enforcer on an unsuspecting Spider-Man!

13.text: Ben Grimm realizes he is a prisoner of his own mind, when things are not as they seem while investigating Doomstadt!

14.text: Spider-Man and Captain Marvel’s team-up continues! The heroes banish the P.R.I.D.E.’s “population control” device to another dimension!

16.text: While in San Francisco, a man named Martin is in trouble and calls on Oliver Cutlass and Typhoon to help. The unusual pair must investigate something called the “Pajusnaya Consignment”.

20.text: The New Mutants and the Hellions have their champions duel for superiority: Cannonball vs. Jetstream!

30.text: The body-snatching Zohar must face the wrath of Moon Knight in this Chicago-set adventure!

31.text: Chris Claremont spills all about the New Mutants.

33.text: With the barbarian Tarianna by his side, Ben approaches another planet's version of Doomstadt.

34.text: Bruce Banner vs. a Hulked-out Max Hammer!

35.text: PRISONERS OF WAR Doctor Doom brings Ultron back online to battle the champions of Earth! Meanwhile, Magneto takes the lone-wolf route!

36.text: Whatever happened to Balder the Brave? In Nornkeep, the fortress carved from living rock, the Norn Queen Karnilla is guarded by many things-a giant wolf-beast chief among them. No man dare tread there, save for one...Balder!

37.text: James Hudson discovers that his life in New York City is too good to be true. His enemy Jerome Jaxon has involved him in an elaborate hoax to join OMEGA FLIGHT!

38.text: A lovers' quarrel! Black Cat isn't sure how she feels about the all-new Spider-Man, but they'll have to hash that out later - if the BLOB doesn't crush them first!

41.text: The New Mutants are trapped by Emma Frost, the White Queen of the Hellfire Club! To make it out alive, they'll have to face off against Emma's team of young mutants, the Hellions!

42.text: WHAT IF…THE HULK WENT BERSERK? In an alternate reality, Bruce Banner doesn't save Rick Jones from the gamma explosion, prompting a chain reaction that affects the Hulk's behavior.

45.text: Black suit Spider-Man and Captain Marvel: Monica Rambeau take on the nefarious P.R.I.D.E.!

46.text: Strange stands off against an unusual threat—while protecting innocents and scrambling for his own survival!

47.text: Ephraim eats a plant growing on a gamma bomb that mutates him into a tree-like creature. When he stumbles across the Defenders headquarters, they must destroy him!

56.text: What will married life be like for Shanna and Ka-Zar?

58.text: Hercules returns to Mount Olympus where Zeus has murdered all the inhabitants. There's only one name left on his hit list: Hercules himself.

59.text: When Hulk returns from the Beyonder's Secret Wars, he discovers that Max Stryker has been using the Gammascope treatment on many people, regardless of knowing any of its long term side effects…

60.text: THE WAR BEGINS Earth's heroes have been whisked away to a mysterious construct in space, but they are not alone. Earth's villains have also appeared. Who is to blame for this meeting of good and evil?
Mike Zeck has gotten some of Marvel's biggest and baddest heroes riled up and looking for a scrape.  You don't want to mess with this bunch, trust us.  The Beyonder learned that the hard way.

61.text: The South Bronx of New York City has never seen anything like the fury and destructive rage of Fafnir the Dragon, who tears apart the neighborhood in a furious search for the Mighty Thor!

62.text: The battle rages on between Sasquatch and the Super Skrull, who was under the guise of Thing from the Fantastic Four!

63.text: Spotlight on the Black Cat! She's looking for her on-and-off lover Spidey, but what she finds is going to change her relationship with him forever!

64.text: While in Battleworld, Ben has his transporter device stolen by one of the Takers!

65.text: Spider-Man is missing! What has happened to the spectacular one? Regardless, Daredevil and the Black Widow must keep working on the pawnbroker murder case in order to prevent an innocent man from going up the river!

67.text: Two villains for the price of one! Beast, Angel and Iceman face off against a mysterious new foe - the WALRUS! But then, they'll have to contend with Frog-Man, who plots to…join the Defenders!?

70.text: With the help of Magik, the New Mutants break into Emma Frost's Massachusetts Academy to save the captive Kitty Pryde and Doug Ramsey!

73.text: Hercules is summoned to Titan, where a dying Apollo warns his brother of their father's insanity.

77.text: At long last…the secret history of Marc Spector’s father! Plus, a reveal at the end of this issue that will leave you gob smacked!

78.text: Spider-Man is back from Battleworld and he's wearing a new suit!  Artist Ron Frenz took the classic pose of Spidey from AMAZING FANTASY #15, made a few adjustments, and the result was a cover almost--if not just as--iconic as the original.

83.text: Ben is tormented over his love for Alicia. His musings are interrupted when Reed calls the Thing into action to investigate strange energies in Central Park…

84.text: Cancer-ridden crime lord Max Stryker forces Bruce Banner to use the Gammascope treatment on him!

85.text: Welcome to Valhalla! Here, in the most revered of Asgard's halls, Odin presides over a group of accomplished mortal warriors after a hard day's fighting. But who is missing from the merrymaking? What disaster awaits the unsuspecting men?

86.text: Dr. Langkowski is forced to reveal his secret identity to his fellow scientists when they are attacked on a research outing!

89.text: The New Mutants throw Professor X a party with the help of Illyana Rasputin. But when the demon S'ym attacks, Illyana and the team must take the fight to his home turf - Limbo!

90.text: WHAT IF…CAPTAIN AMERICA WERE REVIVED TODAY? The 1950s Cap is revived before Steve Rogers.

95.text: Mystical artist Claude von Moore turns his canvas toward a new subject—Doctor Stephen Strange! A commonplace haunting turns into something completely unexpected.

96.text: The final showdown with PROFESSOR POWER of the SECERT EMPIRE! Can the Defenders stop his plan to bring about world devastation?

98.text: Ka-Zar and Shanna have brought peace to Pangea but at the cost of the jungle lord's trust in its people.
